data.text:
The college offers six pre-professional, or pre-health, majors:

Animal Sciences

Biology

Entomology and Nematology

Microbiology and Cell Science

Nutritional Sciences

Wildlife Ecology and Conservation

Each of these majors requires courses needed as prerequisites for admission to programs in medicine, dentistry, veterinary medicine, pharmacy and other health-related programs.

Click here to schedule an advising appointment CALS Pre-health advisor, Kathryn Ivey.
